cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a novel natural language generation task and proposes a new method for generating intermediate sentences. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed method involves training neural networks for generating editing vectors and sentences. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language generation, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a potential category as the proposed method involves the use of recurrent neural networks for generating editing vectors. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of Yelp review dataset, which may involve some visual aspects such as images of the reviewed items.
